author: Jake Lo
text:

author: Fariha Roselan
text:
This AF is not my base gym, I use this gym time to time only. And usually I find the facilities adequate. However, on my visit today, the toilets smell very strongly of pee.  Both toilets.

I understand it's a Sunday and there is no staff/cleaning team etc. Honestly, I don't fully blame the staff as I can see there is a "Toilet Checklist" that they follow.

I call out the culture of the gym goers here. If you can lift heavy, if you can run long distances, but you can't clean up after yourselves.. are you okay?

While you up your PRs, you can also up your social awareness/hygiene. Thank you for your kind attention.

author: Shalesh Prana
text:
A Testament to Incredible Coaching ‚Äì My Fitness Journey

I highly recommend my personal trainer Jannifer  at Anytime Fitness (East Point Mall) for her exceptional dedication and expertise.

Her guidance has been instrumental in helping me get closer to my personal fitness goals. She always prioritizes my safety during our training sessions while still challenging me to push beyond my perceived limits. Her ability to motivate and encourage me, even when I don‚Äôt realize what I‚Äôm capable of, has been truly transformative.

She is a master of her craft, demonstrating both skill and passion in every session. Beyond being an outstanding trainer, she has also been a great source of support and encouragement. I truly appreciate her efforts, both as a coach and as a friend.

The results speak for themselves! After just 7 weeks, I can see and feel the difference. This transformation would not have been possible without her dedication and belief in my potential.

author: Satish Rajaraman
text: Spacious and smartly equipped gym! 4 barbell racks, a smith machine and a lifting platform mean no waiting time to do your weights. Love the recent additions - a linear squat machine and decline press machine. Have never seen any equipment being out of order. The staff and other members are quite amiable and easy going. author: Zinc Tan
text:
The gym is getting seriously cold and overcrowded machines-wise. It used to be simple and functional but perhaps it‚Äôs over subscribed. They also don‚Äôt listen to gym members‚Äô feedback about machines or temperature. The flow of AC is directly blowing at a specific machine.
1. When the temperature is too cold and you‚Äôre exercising, you‚Äôre very prone to injuring yourself.
2. The issue was at a specific machine. They could have very easily moved the machine very slightly (even 10cm) and the flow of AC would be less strong.
3. They could have responded with saying that they‚Äôll check what can be done.
4. They could‚Äôve put something else in place (a shelf?) to diffuse the AC flow.

Updated September 2024:
I have been with the gym since COVID. The machines have gotten increasingly packed and the use of space isn‚Äôt well thought out. They clearly have a lot of patrons and can afford to expand the space to manage this issue. You‚Äôre quite likely to bump into another user, even at emptier timings. Imagine someone bumping into you while working out because they‚Äôre not careful. The machines are also not well-maintained. I‚Äôm often left wondering about my safety. I‚Äôm not sure where my monthly payments are going towards for a service fee? What services are being provided?

This gym was also under renovation for a while and members were not notified via email or sms. Payments were still being deducted despite the lack of access to the gym. Their reasoning was putting up signs at their gym, so users should have known. And yes, I can go elsewhere, but obviously I chose this gym for its location? You should at least offer to freeze payments or make sure there is a blast to all customers. Was it the customer‚Äôs decision to do a renovation despite the potential disruption? No, it was the gym‚Äôs. I‚Äôm sure there might have been customers who were overseas and missed the signage.

Not only all of the above issues, but delayed payment penalties not due to the user‚Äôs end - checked with my credit card - is still the user‚Äôs responsibility to follow up with their payment vendor. And after the gym realised it was an issue for many customers (after one week), they continued to threaten me with an additional late fee (so x2) whilst I was waiting for their payment to respond. All this while, they did not bother to support my request for investigation. In fact, they were dismissive and apathetic to my issue that was caused by them.

Lastly, their website clearly states that anytime fitness clubs are independently owned and operated. Therefore, all of these issues could have been alleviated by this franchise‚Äôs management, but they are actively choosing not to do so.

Don‚Äôt expect any service or support at this gym. Expect the bare minimum, slightly rusty equipment, bad use of space, and smelly restrooms. It used to be a friendly environment where I could head in and say hi to the staff. Now they don‚Äôt care at all and refuse to take responsibility. Honestly all of these issues are way too silly and took too much of my time and energy to even write down. But it‚Äôs exactly because it‚Äôs a completely ridiculous situation that it shouldn‚Äôt have happened and deserves to be recorded for other users to be aware of.

If you‚Äôre looking for a gym in the east, Tampines has 3 AFs, and they were highly responsive. FYI.

author: Dap A
text:
I've been a member of Anytime Fitness for just two months, and I've already faced issues with the EZpay platform used for monthly membership fee deductions. While the staff at Anytime Fitness are polite, the management's insistence on using EZpay, despite numerous customer complaints, is baffling.

In my second month, I was hit with a $15.26 late fee because EZpay claimed my bank rejected the transaction. After checking with my bank, it was clear there were no issues on my end‚Äîno failed, frozen, or rejected transactions. Yet, Anytime Fitness insists I pay the late fee to avoid another charge by the 8th of the month. This is extremely frustrating, especially when no action is taken to resolve this / waive off my fees, and instead, to "force" me to make the late fee asap, otherwise, my access to AF is revoked. Even the staff admitted that refunds / waivers by EZpay after making the late fee payment for customers who were wrongly charged were always unsuccessful. A quick google search on EZpay SG showed that their results are consistently poor, with a 1-star rating and a long history of customer complaints.

EZpay and Anytime Fitness seem to be caught in a blame game, with EZpay pushing the fault onto the merchant and AF pointing fingers back at EZpay. In the end, it's the customer who bears the cost of the late fee THROUGH NO FAULT of ours, which is ridiculous. As a new customer, this leaves a bad taste in my mouth, making me question my decision to join. It's disappointing that Anytime Fitness management continues to use such a flawed platform, putting their customers through unnecessary hassle and fees. AF should reconsider their choice of payment platform soon, or absorb the late fee charges since they are insistent on continuing with this faulty platform.

author: River Chua
text: The existing reviews of this branch are so harsh. I was not excited about visiting this branch because of the reviews, but I had to for the convenience, and was pleasantly surprised. It has all the essential machines and weights you‚Äôd need for a good workout. Granted the barbell area is small, so it will not be suitable for powerlifters. Besides that, they have a good selection of machines and weights, the gym is decently sized, and very clean. When I was here, there was a cleaner wiping down all machines incredibly diligently - much better than I‚Äôve seen with other AFs where just the floors are casually mopped. I also thought the music choices were bops. Visited on a Tuesday afternoon.
